cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.DC 

This paper discusses a decentralized mobile recommender system that relies on data exchange between users in proximity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses data collection, data exchange, and recommender system algorithms, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the challenges and opportunities of the mobile architecture, which could be relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
